           Axios just reported
          </a>
          that SoftBank is filing to raise $500-600mm via SPAC today to acquire a company they haven\xe2\x80\x99t previously invested in \xe2\x80\xa6 like Juul?)
         </em>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Shares of all three companies have \xe2\x80\xa6 lifted off \xe2\x80\xa6 since the mergers were announced. DraftKings is leading the pack, up 403% YTD, followed by Opendoor at 259% and Virgin Galactic at 106%.
        </p>
